    --><!-- Moderation --><!--
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_UserApprove_SubHeader">User Approve</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_UserApprove_Instructions">Use this tab to establish the moderator+ limited actions a user requests and requires mod approval to perform.\nModActionType-the type of defined action-a command, channel point redeem, etc\nModActionName-the name of the action based on the type. e.g. Type=command, Name=setuserintro\nModPerformType-the type of action to perform, to specify a name that may exist in different contexts, e.g. a command-!raid.\nModPerformAction-the name of the action to perform once approved\nThe default channel point approval takes user supplied text and submits it to a specific command, eg. "!command 'username' 'channelpoint text'".</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_ModActionType_Column">ModActionType</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_ModActionName_Column">ModActionName</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_ModPerformType_Column">ModPerformType</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_ModPerformAction_Column">ModPerformAction</system:String>

    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_MsgMod_SubHeader">Msg Mod</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Moderation_MsgMod_Instructions">Use this tab to manage bot moderation settings, such as banning users based on their chat messages or chat activity. To identify a message for action, the bot needs a group of similar messages so a new message can be reviewed and identified.\nThis procedure uses Machine Learning (hence the 'training'); and uses "BagOfWords" to convert messages (strings into number vectors) such that the "Naive Bayes" classifier can probabilistically determine if a message falls within the same range of trained messages already identified as spam or harrassment.\nCaution, the messages of hate and spam need to be included here so similar message can be identified as hate or spam.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_Id_Column">Id</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_MsgType_Column">Msg Type</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_BanReason_Column">BanReason</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_TimeoutNote">Timeout is marked in seconds, minimum is 1 and max is 1,209,600 (2 weeks).\nWhen 'ModAction' is set to 'Ban', the timeout isn't used.\nIt's probable sometimes messages from long term followers/users are a little more tolerable than new arrivals, options provided for to help with this.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_ModAction_Column">ModAction</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_TimeoutSecs_Column">Timeout Secs</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_ViewerTypes_Column">Viewer Types</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Data_Mod_LearningMessage_Column">Learning Message</system:String>

